<br>
A friend of mine (shaman) and I went to CC to do a little farming one day... we both had some alts we wanted to twink.<br>
<br>
Well, he brought up that pet of his and owned the place!  I wasn't even needed!  After that, I thought to myself, I want to play ultimate pet class.<br>
<br>
I started my mage that very day, and never looked back.  I play him almost daily, to the point where my druid is getting sorely neglected.  He levels like nobody's business.  Yesterday, he made 34.  The nukes he gets are icing on the cake.  I expect in a month or so my lil' ol' mage will be grouping with the friends I made as a druid.<br>
<br>
I can't wait! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufandarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fandarian</A> at: 12/20/01 10:07:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhelxo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Helxo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.gifs.net/animate/ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(12/29/01 6:08:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm31.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.raph.com/3dartists/artgallery/zach1.jpg height=100 weidth=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you  make a mage?</span><hr size=1> I wanted to be like you Iwka =) <br>
